{
  "texts": [
    "While AI holds theoretical promise for revolutionary feats, its impact hinges on its application and capacity to disrupt existing systems.",
    "This contextual dependence results in varied impacts across diverse applications and fields, as elucidated by Horowitz et al. [34].",
    "Furthermore, individual reactions to AI vary widely, influenced by personal history, upbringing, and location.",
    "Even government personnel may undergo behavioral changes in response to the availability of AI systems, potentially impacting the data and procedures upon which these systems rely.Understanding and predicting public reactions to AI pose significant challenges, as acknowledged in prior research by Bundy [16].",
    "Consequently, a nuanced understanding of specific AI systems becomes imperative for impact evaluations."
  ]
}